    "message_1": "Solve the following system of linear equations using matrix methods:\n\n- 3x + 4y - 2z = 8\n- 2x - 5y + 3z = -32\n- x + 2y - z = 5\n\nExpress your final answer in the form of (x, y, z).",
    "message_2": "First, we write the system of linear equations in matrix form AX = B, where A is the matrix of coefficients, X is the column matrix of variables (x, y, z), and B is the column matrix of constants.\n\nA = | -3  4 -2 |\n    |  2 -5  3 |\n    |  1  2 -1 |\n\nX = | x |\n    | y |\n    | z |\n\nB = |  8  |\n    | -32 |\n    |  5  |\n\nNow, we can find the inverse of matrix A, and then multiply it by matrix B to find the values of x, y, and z.\n\nA^(-1) = 1/det(A) * adj(A)\n\nFirst, we find the determinant of A:\n\ndet(A) = -3(-5*-1 - 3*2) - 4(2*-1 - 3*1) + 2(2*2 - 5*1)\n       = -3(-5 + 6) - 4(-2 - 3) + 2(4 - 5)\n       = -3(1) + 4(5) + 2(-1)\n       = -3 + 20 - 2\n       = 15\n\nNow, we find the adjugate of A:\n\nadj(A) = | (-5*-1 - 3*2)  -(2*-1 - 3*1)  (2*2 - 5*1) |\n         | -(4*-1 - 2*2)   (-3*-1 - 2*1) -(4*1 - 3*2)|\n         |  (4*3 - 5*2)    -(1*3 - 2*1)   (-3*2 - 4*1)|\n\nadj(A) = |  5  -1   4  |\n         |  2   1  -2  |\n         |  2  -1  -10 |\n\nNow, we find the inverse of A:\n\nA^(-1) = 1/15 * adj(A)\n\nA^(-1) = |  1/3  -1/15  4/15  |\n         |  2/15  1/15 -2/15  |\n         |  2/15 -1/15 -2/3   |\n\nNow, we multiply A^(-1) by B:\n\nX = A^(-1) * B\n\nX = |  1/3  -1/15  4/15  | |  8  |\n    |  2/15  1/15 -2/15  | | -32 |\n    |  2/15 -1/15 -2/3   | |  5  |\n\nX = | (1/3)*8 + (-1/15)*(-32) + (4/15)*5  |\n    | (2/15)*8 + (1/15)*(-32) + (-2/15)*5 |\n    | (2/15)*8 + (-1/15)*(-32) + (-2/3)*5 |\n\nX = | 8/3 + 32/15 + 20/15 |\n    | 16/15 - 32/15 - 10/15|\n    | 16/15 + 32/15 - 10/3 |\n\nX = | 24/15 + 32/15 + 20/15 |\n    | -26/15 |\n    | 48/15 - 50/15 |\n\nX = | 76/15 |\n    | -26/15 |\n    | -2/15  |\n\nSo, the solution to the system of linear equations is (x, y, z) = (76/15, -26/15, -2/15)."
